    "casingNote": "Column keys are the lowercase Parquet names. dbisamName is the real stored case in live Exportmaster (DBISAM), harvested via ODBC. Both backends are case-INSENSITIVE in SQL, so either casing resolves on either; keep all column references inside the SQL string (Power Query M field access is case-SENSITIVE, so never field-access a source column)."

